                {"src": "ellicott", "attr": "Ellicott's Commentary", "html": "<p>With power — that is, in a transcendent and superhuman manner. According to the spirit of holiness — in antithesis to \"according to the flesh,\" and therefore coming where we should expect \"in his divine nature.\" The resurrection is the event by which Christ's divine sonship was installed in a new mode of power. He was Son of God before; now he is declared Son of God in power — regnant, victorious, enthroned.</p>"},
